scripts.text:
You stand before a colourful swirling phenomenon that is clearly a magical gateway of some sort, not dissimilar to the minor Gates that you used to travel between the Domains of the First Realm.

There is no immediate indication of where this one leads...

Coming from behind this door is a faint hum. You pause to listen for a few moments, but no explanation is readily apparent.
The pool of water in the alcove is deeper than the rest. You can't see the bottom, but you can see some movement beneath the surface...

Peering through the gloom, you can make out several large, pale eels circling lazily in the dark waters. 

They don't look dangerous. If you're quick enough, you may be able to grab one of them.

scripts.text:
Here you find a small stone shrine.

Shrines of the type are usually dedicated to Garret, The Grey Wayfarer, the ambivalent patron of heroes, adventurers and wayfarers; the cloaked one who stands guard before those who watch their own backs.
The portcullis is firmly closed. You do not see an obvious mechanism to open it...

Beneath the water of the shallow pool you spot a wide crack between the paving stones.

The crack is too dark and crooked to see anything. You could put an arm deep inside and explore, if you wanted to...

scripts.title: Explore the hole with your arm?

scripts.text:
The large lever mechanism looks tarnished and old but otherwise functional.

You wonder what hidden machinery it connects to...
GATEHOUSE

On the far wall of this large room you see what looks like two deactivated inter-domain portals. 

Before you can move over to get a close look, something else draws your urgent attention...

Shallow puddles dot this area of gloomy passageways, and the air is cold and humid.

You wonder where the leak is.
GATEHOUSE
A pile of dry and dusty bones has been heaped in this dark corner.

You brush cobwebs aside and peer nervously through the darkness. This area smells of mold, dust and fungus.

A spider, larger than the others, rouses itself angrily from a nest of bones in the far corner and moves to attack!

You brush cobwebs aside and peer nervously through the darkness. This area smells of mold, dust and fungus.

A spider, larger than the others, rouses itself angrily from a nest of bones in the far corner and moves to attack!
Swarming from the surrounding webbing, you are attacked by a group of disturbingly large spiders!
Something about this room seems intangibly different... maybe the air currents?
Large silky webs cover the walls and recede around the corner.
Swarming from the surrounding webbing, you are attacked by a group of disturbingly large spiders!
The portcullis is lowered and will not budge. You note a small lock mechanism with a keyhole near the ground...

This area of the dungeon is even dustier, gloomier and more run down than what you have seen so far.

From the darkness you seem to feel many eyes watching you through the strands of webbing.
A large web has been spun across the entrance to this alcove.
Unsurprisingly, the creator of the web is unimpressed with your intrusion.

You find a pile of very ancient very dry bones.
Maybe you should search them more carefully...
From behind the door you hear faint scraping and rustling noises.
This mushrooms growing in this corner look a bit different...
The darkness here is relieved only by occasional luminous fungi. An earthen floor crunches under your feet, and the air is dank and heavy.
In a corner of the room you find a number of large, chitinous egg sacs.
These bones feel brittle and dry to the touch. Maybe you should search them more carefully...

maskTextureMouseClickScript.text:
Someone has carved a few lines in the stone wall here.

"Azael was here. A journey of a thousand leagues starts with one step."
